# Domain: CircuitPython Multi-Experiment Workspace

## Scope

Embedded development with **CircuitPython** across multiple hardware experiments under `/Users/alex/Development/VsCode/CircuitPython/`. Each experiment is a folder named `YYYY-MM_ExpNN_<descriptor>/`. A shared toolbox lives in `CircuitPy-VsCode-Tooling/`.

This rule sets the domain skeleton: the categories that organize CircuitPython knowledge (now stored in the `concepts/` graph + per-project `CONCLUSIONS.md` â€” see below), what conventions are house-style, and what status defaults apply.

All entries default to `unverified` unless specified otherwise. Code references include experiment name + relative path + (when relevant) commit/branch.

## Active Project Detection (M1)

> **Post-warm-reset (2026-06-14)**: "experiment" is now a **project** under a **family** (this CircuitPython work is family `circuitpython`; Bamboo-Lamp is its own family). The authoritative detector and path-globs live in **`memory/projects/_INDEX.md`** (M1). Treat `experiment` and `project` as synonyms when reading older entries.

Detect the active project by matching the most-recently-edited / open file path against the **path-globs in `projects/_INDEX.md`** (e.g. `2026-04_Exp14_*/**` â†’ `circuitpython-exp14-display`; `Bamboo-Lamp/**` â†’ `bamboo-lamp`). Read + write only that project's `projects/<slug>/` folder (+ shared `universal/*`, `concepts/_INDEX.md`, central `SESSION_LOG.md`). If a path matches none or is ambiguous, **ask before writing per-project memory** â€” mis-routing into the wrong project's memory is the top failure mode (M1). Full routing procedure: `04-multi-project.mdc Â§ Placement gate`.

## Domain knowledge â†’ concept graph (replaces the old `TECHNICAL.md` schema)

Post-warm-reset, domain knowledge is **not** stored in a monolithic per-project `TECHNICAL.md`. It lives in the **concept graph** (`memory/concepts/`, D8): one `concepts/<domain>.md` per evidenced domain, indexed by `concepts/_INDEX.md`, related by `concepts/_RELATIONS.md`. Seed a domain only on evidence (C7); split a domain to per-concept files only when it grows unwieldy (graduation rule).

The categories below are **organizing lenses / candidate concept domains** (not storage sections): Terminology Â· Boards & MCUs (+ pin maps) Â· CircuitPython Library Map Â· Hardware-Interfacing Patterns Â· Pin / Peripheral Assumptions Â· Toolchain Â· Code Map Â· Verification Queue. Seeded domains today: `circuitpython-runtime`, `fonts` (see `concepts/_INDEX.md`); candidate-but-unseeded: `power`, `i2c`, `deep-sleep`, `led-driving`, `display`, `fuel-gauge`, `tooling`. A per-concept "Verification Queue" lives inside the relevant `concepts/<domain>.md`.

## CONCLUSIONS.md Conventions

Status tiers (per `00-memory-system.mdc` Â§ Evidence-Status Discipline):
- `unverified` â€” stated but not investigated
- `evidence-supported` â€” corroborated by independent sources (datasheets, official CircuitPython docs, on-device behavior, mechanical verification â€” grep/AST/tests)
- `disputed` â€” conflicting evidence; record both positions
- `invalidated` â€” disproven; retain with correction history

No separate human-elevation tier on this workspace â€” the user is project owner across experiments but not the CircuitPython domain authority. Promotion depends on independent corroboration. When the user *is* the authority (project conventions, design intent, what success means), use the *contradictions have no default winner* adjudication path in `WORKING_STYLE.md`.

Tag every conclusion with its experiment scope: `[exp14]`, `[exp13]`, `[tooling]`, `[cross-experiment]`, `[universal]`.

When a finding holds across 2+ experiments, note it as `[cross-experiment]` and consider whether to promote a derived directive into `universal/WORKING_STYLE.md` (or a pattern into `universal/PATTERNS.md`) via the `crossref/BY_PATTERN.md` ladder (M3).

## House Conventions

- **No code edits to vendored libraries** in `lib/` â€” those are versioned copies of upstream bundle libraries. Modifications belong in experiment-local code.
- **Settings layering**: workspace-level `.code-workspace` settings provide defaults; per-experiment `.vscode/settings.json` overrides board-specific items. VS Code does **not** merge arrays â€” `python.analysis.extraPaths` defined per experiment fully overrides the workspace-level value.
- **Credentials in `settings.toml`** â€” never commit. Listed in `.gitignore`.
- **Bundle archives** under `bundles/` and `libArchive/` are gitignored; treat as re-downloadable.
- **CIRCUITPY drive**: when present, treat as the deployment target; never edit files there as a source of truth â€” they are deploys from the experiment's local source.

